label: TYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code that identifies the type of Lookup record.

label: NUMBER
description: This field stores the value used to look up the account.

label: IDTYPE
description: This field stores a code that indicates if the lookup refers to a specific Share or Loan record.

label: ID
description: This field stores the ID of the Share or Loan record this lookup refers to.

label: RECORDCHANGEDATE
description: The system stores the system date in this field when you create, change, or save the Lookup record. Sometimes the system updates this field because the record was saved, even though there may not be any actual changes in the record.

label: LOCATOR
description: This field stores a unique number within each member account that can be used as a unique identification of this record.
